-- BioLineRx Falls Most in 2 Weeks, Narrows Gap With U.S. Stock
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-02-07T15:03:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-07/biolinerx-falls-most-in-2-weeks-narrows-gap-with-u-s-stock-1-.html
BioLineRx Ltd.  slid the most in
almost two weeks, narrowing the gap with the biophamaceutical
company’s American depositary receipts.  The  shares slumped  11 percent, the most since Jan. 26, to
1.66 shekels, or the equivalent of 45 cents, at the 4:30 p.m.
close in  Tel Aviv . The company’s ADRs, each representing 10
shares, closed at $4.44 yesterday in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
